---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';

const metaDescription = "Learn microservices architecture and AI agent integration through a real-world Personal Finance Management System. Practical guides on Domain-Driven Design, event-driven architecture, service mesh, and AI-ready microservices for FinTech and SaaS applications.";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={metaDescription} />
		<meta name="keywords" content="microservices architecture, AI agents, domain-driven design, Spring Boot, NestJS, Kafka" />
		<link rel="canonical" href="edsa.tech" />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<article>
				<!-- Hero Section & Image Placeholder -->
				<section class="hero-section">
					<div class="hero-text">
						<h1>Build Production-Ready Microservices & AI-Powered Systems üöÄ</h1>
						<p class="subtitle">
							Learn through a real-world <strong>Personal Finance Management System</strong> built with 10+ microservices, event-driven architecture, and AI-ready design patterns.
						</p>
					</div>
					<!-- Placeholder for your Hero Image -->
					<div class="hero-image-placeholder">
						<!-- You can replace this div with a proper <img> tag once you choose an image URL -->
						<!-- Example: <img src="../../assets/PFMS-architectural-diagram.png" alt="Illustration of a cloud-native microservice architecture" /> -->
						<p><em>[Insert your architecture hero image here]</em></p>
					</div>
				</section>

				<hr />

				<!-- <section>
					<h2>From FinTech Engineer to Your Learning Companion ü§ù</h2>
					<p>
						I've recently joined the FinTech industry and I'm sharing everything I've learned about building scalable, resilient microservices. This isn't theory‚Äîit's battle-tested architecture patterns from a production-grade personal finance system.
					</p>
				</section> -->

				<section>
					<h2>The PFMS Project: Your Microservices Playground üõ∞Ô∏è</h2>
					<p>The <strong>Personal Finance Management System (PFMS)</strong> demonstrates enterprise-grade patterns across a polyglot stack:</p>
					
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Multi-Language Ecosystem:</strong> Spring Boot, NestJS, Go, Python, and React.</li>
						<li><strong>Event-Driven Architecture:</strong> Kafka for async communication and RabbitMQ for message brokering.</li>
						<li><strong>Service Discovery & Config:</strong> Eureka and Consul registry with a Git-backed Config Server.</li>
						<li><strong>Security & Observability:</strong> JWT authentication, custom actuators, and health monitoring.</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>What You'll Master Here üí°</h2>
					
					<h3>For Developers Leveling Up üìà</h3>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Domain-Driven Design (DDD):</strong> Mapping bounded contexts to financial microservices.</li>
						<li><strong>Event-driven patterns:</strong> Kafka integration and async processing after DB commits.</li>
						<li><strong>Polyglot persistence:</strong> PostgreSQL, MySQL, and database-per-service design.</li>
						<li><strong>API Gateway patterns:</strong> Routing, load balancing, and JWT security.</li>
					</ul>
					
					<h3>AI-Ready Architecture (Coming Soon) ü§ñ</h3>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>AI agent integration patterns</strong> for financial workflows.</li>
						<li><strong>Microservices as AI interfaces:</strong> Exposing services for LLM consumption.</li>
						<li><strong>RAG systems for financial data:</strong> Vector stores and context-aware AI.</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Microservices Architecture: The Foundation üèóÔ∏è</h2>
					<p>
						Instead of a "monolith," microservices break applications into independent services that communicate through APIs and events. This enables:
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Independent Deployment:</strong> Update the Budget Service without touching others.</li>
						<li><strong>Selective Scaling:</strong> Scale only the services under heavy load.</li>
						<li><strong>Technology Flexibility:</strong> Use the best tool (Java, Node, Go) for each specific job.</li>
						<li><strong>AI Integration Ready:</strong> Add LLM capabilities to individual services independently.</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Start Learning from Real Code üëá</h2>
					<p>
						<a href="/blog"><strong>[ Read the Blog ]</strong></a> &nbsp; 
						<a href="https://github.com/delose/personal-finance-management-system" target="_blank"><strong>[ Explore the Code ]</strong></a>
					</p>
				</section>

				<footer>
					<p><em>Written by a FinTech engineer focused on scalable microservices and AI value. Connect on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/delose/" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a>.</em></p>
				</footer>
			</article>
		</main>
		<Footer />

		<style>
			main {
				width: 100%;
				max-width: 900px; /* Slightly wider main content area */
				margin: auto;
				padding: 1em;
				color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
			}
			h1, h2, h3 {
				color: rgb(var(--black));
			}
			section {
				margin-bottom: 3rem;
			}
			hr {
				border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
				margin: 2rem 0;
			}
			.hero-section {
				display: flex;
				justify-content: space-between;
				align-items: center;
				gap: 2rem;
				margin-bottom: 3rem;
			}
			.hero-text {
				flex: 1;
			}
			.hero-image-placeholder {
				flex: 1;
				background-color: #f0f4f8;
				padding: 2rem;
				border-radius: 8px;
				text-align: center;
				min-height: 200px; /* Ensure space for the image */
				display: flex;
				align-items: center;
				justify-content: center;
				border: 1px dashed #ccc;
			}

			/* Basic responsiveness for mobile */
			@media (max-width: 768px) {
				.hero-section {
					flex-direction: column;
					text-align: center;
				}
				.hero-image-placeholder {
					width: 100%;
				}
			}
		</style>
	</body>
</html>
